<p><strong><a href="/scp-4338">SCP-4338</a> - Vulcan, the Disaster</strong><br />
<em>Ancient problems require modern solutions.</em><br />
[<span class="odate time_1562082900 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">02 Jul 2019 15:55</span>] [<span style="color: green">+349</span>] [Comments: 64] [Last Comment: <span class="odate time_1586253529 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">07 Apr 2020 09:58</span>]</p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">►&nbsp;Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">&nbsp;▼&nbsp;Close</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<blockquote>
<p>I've struggled with my my eating habits for a very, very long time. I have a very addictive personality. While writing &quot;Karma Kameleon&quot;, I started craving something to snack on. Candy. Chips. Crackers. Something pre-packaged and easy to binge. That compulsion nearly dragged me out the door, even though I knew I'd end up feeling bloated, empty, and ashamed. It's a struggle I feel a majority of people share. I tried translating that feeling into a story and, well, Vulcan was born.</p>
</blockquote>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="/scp-4228">SCP-4228</a> - Karma Kameleon</strong><br />
<em>Loving would be easy if your colors were like my dreams</em><br />
[<span class="odate time_1559667755 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">04 Jun 2019 17:02</span>] [<span style="color: green">+229</span>] [Comments: 40] [Last Comment: <span class="odate time_1573495403 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">11 Nov 2019 18:03</span>]</p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">►&nbsp;Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">&nbsp;▼&nbsp;Close</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<blockquote>
<p>The ennui protocol has always been one of my favorite concepts in the SCP, this idea of a last resort &quot;wipe the slate clean&quot; scenario that's only performed when humanity has lost something so precious, removing our collective memory of it is a mercy. I've also worked in children's media production for 3 years. That definitely shaped this article. I struggled a lot to pin down the format for this piece. The narrative flow is still a bit jagged at the edges, but I'm happy with it.</p>
</blockquote>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="/scp-4281">SCP-4281</a> - Stalled Conversation</strong><br />
<em>Unseen insight in the oddest of places. (My first article!)</em><br />
[<span class="odate time_1556719084 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">01 May 2019 13:58</span>] [<span style="color: green">+317</span>] [Comments: 41] [Last Comment: <span class="odate time_1586833004 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">14 Apr 2020 02:56</span>]</p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">►&nbsp;Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">&nbsp;▼&nbsp;Close</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<blockquote>
<p>Where I work, there's a small 4-stall dedicated bathroom for our floor. Every time I'm in there, EVERY TIME, the furthest stall is closed. I never know if it's occupied, or just shut. So there I am, pondering it in silence, and when I finally decide it must just be closed I hear a cough, or a sneaker squeak. It's Schrodingers stall! I consider myself a high-output introvert, someone who can be very sociable and smooth talking for short periods, but needs a long recharge period alone. Useful during job interviews, not so much for conferences. People assume you've got it together, chatting and cracking jokes, but it can be pretty isolating. I wanted to put that feeling into a character, with all the absurdity intact.</p>
</blockquote>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="/scp-4938">SCP-4938</a> - Sweat from the Sun</strong><br />
<em>&quot;It's to keep the town alive.&quot; she said. &quot;We need gold to keep this town alive.&quot;</em><br />
[<span class="odate time_1564668930 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">01 Aug 2019 14:15</span>] [<span style="color: green">+144</span>] [Comments: 32] [Last Comment: <span class="odate time_1567506692 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">03 Sep 2019 10:31</span>]</p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">►&nbsp;Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">&nbsp;▼&nbsp;Close</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>I was inspired to write this when researching neutron stars. <em>It is currently theorized that heavy elements such as platinum, uranium and gold are created when two neutron stars collide. This celestial collision will cause an explosion, tearing them apart, and scattering their metals throughout the universe.</em> I wanted to try and write another &quot;deeper mystery&quot; style article again. It's much trickier for me, but that makes it better writing practice.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="/scp-4978">SCP-4978</a> - BROOK TOWN BEAT DOWN</strong><br />
<em>Love, pugilism, and protocol in a snowy little slice of America.</em><br />
[<span class="odate time_1567352952 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">01 Sep 2019 15:49</span>] [<span style="color: green">+183</span>] [Comments: 53] [Last Comment: <span class="odate time_1578188393 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">05 Jan 2020 01:39</span>]</p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">►&nbsp;Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">&nbsp;▼&nbsp;Close</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>This article was influenced by the Warriors, Letterkenny, and countless cartoons. After the bleak tone set by <em>Sweat from the Sun</em>, I wanted to go back to writing more funny, upbeat articles. Plus, there's only been a handful of SCPs that write a nice, charming love-story that involves the anomaly in some way. I can understand why not many people try and tackle this subject, but I thought I'd give it a shot. Hopefully, this is as fun to read as it was to write.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="/scp-4382">SCP-4382</a> - Entropic of Hulwick</strong><br />
<em>Perpetual motion in a perpetually autumn town.</em><br />
[<span class="odate time_1569985776 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">02 Oct 2019 03:09</span>] [<span style="color: green">+202</span>] [Comments: 40] [Last Comment: <span class="odate time_1572681987 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">02 Nov 2019 08:06</span>]</p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">►&nbsp;Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">&nbsp;▼&nbsp;Close</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>For the month of October, I had a much different, much more horror-themed article in mind. The scope of it got away from me, and the SCP lore involved meant a lot more research time. September 27th rolled up, and I had nothing ready to post. Then, when listening to Far Caspian, I had the idea for 4382. That, in turn, lead me to an idea for a series, but that's a different story. Hulwick was based off my experiences in Algiers, New Orleans. My father and I visited there while on vacation. All the decorations and empty streets made me feel like I was walking through an autumn postcard. I hope you enjoy it.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="/scp-5055">SCP-5055</a> - Pandora</strong><br />
<em>What is most important when the world is ending?</em><br />
[<span class="odate time_1579566983 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">21 Jan 2020 00:36</span>] [<span style="color: green">+206</span>] [Comments: 34] [Last Comment: <span class="odate time_1607693715 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">11 Dec 2020 13:35</span>]</p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">►&nbsp;Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">&nbsp;▼&nbsp;Close</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>My entry for the 5k contest. A collection of apocalyptic tales based around both the Pandoras box and Four Horsemen mythos. Also a play on the &quot;there is no canon&quot; concept of the Foundation, wherein all these realities presented could be true, or none of them might be. All that matters, the only mystery they present worth solving isn't &quot;what's in the box?&quot; but a question all good apocalyptic fiction asks: what about the world is worth saving? When the planet itself is a burning house, what do we grab on the way out while letting everything else burn? This was a bit outside my usual wheelhouse, and played pretty fast and loose with the format, and GOD did I have next to no time for editing, but I'm happy with it.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="/scp-5858">SCP-5858</a> - The Kindness of Strangers</strong><br />
<em>I'm sure it picks up by the 2,000th act.</em><br />
[<span class="odate time_1581544540 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">12 Feb 2020 21:55</span>] [<span style="color: green">+343</span>] [Comments: 43] [Last Comment: <span class="odate time_1590812060 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">30 May 2020 04:14</span>]</p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">►&nbsp;Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">&nbsp;▼&nbsp;Close</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Another foray into the world of Xi-5, and the newly minted &quot;Locked Scenarios&quot;. I see this kind of anomalous repetition often in science fiction, horror, and of course SCP canon. It needed some solid faux-science to pin it down, because what else is the Foundation good for? I came up with this one based off a real-life experience when I was younger, coupled with some influences from my Drama days. I hope you enjoy!</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="/scp-5579">SCP-5579</a> - Boba Roe</strong><br />
<em>Tapioca is alien eggs! And soylent green is high in cholesterol!</em><br />
[<span class="odate time_1586911403 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">15 Apr 2020 00:43</span>] [<span style="color: green">+196</span>] [Comments: 53] [Last Comment: <span class="odate time_1592765404 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">21 Jun 2020 18:50</span>]</p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">►&nbsp;Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">&nbsp;▼&nbsp;Close</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<blockquote>
<p>I don't like tapioca. They're slimy and squishy and resemble gigantified caviar. My partner, however, loves them, and all derivatives of bubble tea. They also make a point of slurping them loudly whenever possible, and as close to my ear as possible. Like all my articles, this vaguely indescribable feeling of discomfort and disgust needed to be turned into a writing project, because where the heck else am I going to derive inspiration from? The majesty of nature? On your bike.</p>
</blockquote>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-1" style="display:none"><div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="/a-fond-farewell">A Fond Farewell</a> - or How I Learned to Stop Investigating and Love the Amnestic</strong><br />
<em>There's more to a man than just his memories.</em><br />
[<span class="odate time_1550780330 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">21 Feb 2019 20:18</span>] [<span style="color: green">+41</span>] [Comments: 5] [Last Comment: <span class="odate time_1559578571 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">03 Jun 2019 16:16</span>]</p>
